# PART 6 — Backend Deployment

## Update Ubuntu
sudo apt update


## Install Node.js, npm, Git

sudo apt install nodejs npm git -y


Verify:

node -v
npm -v


## Clone GitHub Repo

git clone https://github.com/PranavDeshmane3434/CloudComputing.git
---

## Enter Backend Folder

cd cloudComputing/backend



## Install Packages

npm install


---

## Create `.env`

nano .env

Paste:

MONGO_URI=YOUR_MONGODB_URI
PORT=5000
```



## Start Backend

npm start



---



---




# PART 8 — Frontend Deployment

## Update Ubuntu

sudo apt update
```

---

## Install Node.js, npm, Git

sudo apt install nodejs npm git -y
```

---

## Clone Repo

git clone https://github.com/PranavDeshmane3434/CloudComputing.git

---

## Enter Frontend Folder


cd CloudComputing/frontend
```

---

## Install Packages

npm install
```

---

## Create `.env`

nano .env
```

Paste backend IP:

```env id="t5r8wc"
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://BACKEND_PUBLIC_IP:5000
```

Example:

```env id="j9k4qn"
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://13.233.xx.xx:5000
```


## Start Frontend

npm start
```

